# Maintain ship-and-deploy skill

If you edit any file that affects staging, committing, pushing, or deployment:

1. Read [.cursor/skills/ship-and-deploy/SKILL.md](../skills/ship-and-deploy/SKILL.md).
2. Run:

   ```bash
   .cursor/skills/ship-and-deploy/scripts/audit-sources.sh
   ```

3. When the audit reports **STALE** sources (or you changed deploy behavior):
   - Update [.cursor/skills/ship-and-deploy/reference.md](../skills/ship-and-deploy/reference.md) with new commands, ports, or hooks.
   - Adjust [.cursor/skills/ship-and-deploy/SKILL.md](../skills/ship-and-deploy/SKILL.md) if the workflow changed.
   - Set `last_audited_commit` in [MANIFEST.json](../skills/ship-and-deploy/MANIFEST.json) to current `HEAD` (short or full hash).
   - Bump `version` in MANIFEST when deploy steps or safety rules change.
   - Append a dated row to [CHANGELOG.md](../skills/ship-and-deploy/CHANGELOG.md).

Include skill maintenance in the same commit/PR as the setup change whenever possible so the workflow stays traceable.

When updating deploy behavior, always preserve:
- **Production data safety** — no volume wipes, no unnecessary restarts of Postgres/SeaweedFS
- **Scoped redeploy default** — rebuild only services affected by the diff

Do **not** duplicate long command lists in this rule — keep details in the skill reference file.
